{{Messianic Judaism}}
The '''Messianic Israel Alliance''' ('''MIA''') serves the Messianic community as an organization for [[Messianic Jews]] and other [[Christians]]. Particular emphasis is placed on the [[divinity]] of Jesus, observation of the ''[[Shabbat]]'' (Sabbath) from sundown on Friday to sundown on Saturday, and celebration of the [[Jewish festivals|Biblical Festivals]] and following of [[Jewish dietary laws]]. [[Christianity]] and [[Judaism]] have long associated the term "[[Children of Israel|Israel]]" with their followers. The Messianic Israel Alliance was founded in 1999 as a service organization for [[Christians]] who were interested in the Hebraic foundations of Christianity. <ref>[http://www.messianicisrael.com/ The Messianic Israel Alliance - About us<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

